This paper focuses on stereo matching using convolutional neural networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new network architecture and a multi-task learning approach, which are both related to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of context information and edge detection, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on stereo benchmarks, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
